</div>
<button class="accordion">Is yelling in the workplace harassment?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>The short answer is yes. Legally speaking, supervisors and managers are allowed to yell at employees. However, when yelling is about or against a protected class, the yelling may qualify as harassment.</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">How does workplace harassment make you feel?</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>It makes people feel uncomfortable, sad, or bad about themselves. It is unwelcome and unwanted. So the most significant indicator of workplace harassment is how you, as the recipient, feel about what is being said or done. Sometimes attention that is exciting and good from one person is unwanted from another.</p>
